<blog>
# SnapEvent Landing Page Project Analysis

## 1. Project Introduction

### Purpose Statement
SnapEvent is a Next.js-based platform designed to connect clients with professional photographers. The application facilitates photographer discovery, portfolio browsing, booking management, and onboarding for new photographers.

### Core Goals and Objectives
- Provide an intuitive landing page for discovering photographers
- Enable seamless booking experiences for clients
- Streamline photographer onboarding and profile creation
- Offer comprehensive portfolio management tools for photographers
- Implement a robust authentication and authorization system

### Target Audience
- Clients seeking professional photography services
- Professional photographers looking to expand their client base
- Photography enthusiasts browsing portfolios
- Event planners and coordinators

## 2. Technical Architecture

### Component Breakdown
The project follows a Next.js application structure with a clear separation of concerns:

```mermaid
flowchart TD
  A[Client] --> B[API Layer]
  B --> C[Business Logic]
  C --> D[Data Access]
  D --> E[(Supabase Database)]
```

### Design Patterns
- Component-based architecture using React
- API routes for server-side operations
- Context management for state
- Modular component organization
- Type-safe development with TypeScript

### System Relationships
The application architecture demonstrates a clean separation between frontend components and backend services:

```mermaid
graph TD
  App[App Component] --> Header[Header]
  App --> Router[Router]
  Router --> LandingPage[LandingPage]
  Router --> OnboardingForm[OnboardingForm]
  Router --> PortfolioPage[PortfolioPage]
  LandingPage --> Search[Search Functionality]
  OnboardingForm --> API[API Integration]
  PortfolioPage --> BookingCalendar[BookingCalendar]
  PortfolioPage --> AvailabilityManager[AvailabilityManager]
  PortfolioPage --> BookingManager[BookingManager]
```

### Data Flow
The data flow follows a unidirectional pattern from API to components:

```mermaid
flowchart TD
  A[API Routes] --> B[lib/api.ts]
  B --> C[Component State]
  C --> D[UI Components]
  D --> E[User Interaction]
  E --> F[API Calls]
  F --> A
```

## 3. Key Implementation

### Main Entry Points
- `src/components/LandingPage.tsx` - Primary landing page component
- `src/components/OnboardingForm.tsx` - Photographer onboarding flow
- `src/components/PortfolioPage.tsx` - Photographer portfolio display
- `pages/index.tsx` - Application entry point

### Core Modules
- `src/lib/api.ts` - API service layer for HTTP requests
- `src/lib/supabase.ts` - Supabase client configuration
- `src/components/BookingCalendar.tsx` - Interactive booking system
- `src/components/AvailabilityManager.tsx` - Photographer availability management
- `src/components/BookingManager.tsx` - Booking request management

### Configuration Approach
- `next.config.js` - Next.js configuration
- `tailwind.config.js` - Tailwind CSS configuration
- `package.json` - Dependency management
- Environment variables for Supabase configuration

### External Dependencies
- `@supabase/supabase-js` - Database and authentication
- `framer-motion` - Animation library
- `lucide-react` - Icon library
- `react-hook-form` - Form management
- `prisma` - Database ORM

### Integration Points
- Supabase authentication and database
- API routes in `pages/api/`
- Environment variable configuration
- Third-party libraries for UI components

### Component Relationships
The component architecture demonstrates a hierarchical relationship:

```mermaid
graph LR
  A[LandingPage] --> B[Search Functionality]
  A --> C[Trending Photographers]
  A --> D[Category Browsing]
  B --> E[api/photographers]
  C --> E
  D --> E
  F[OnboardingForm] --> G[UserTypeSelection]
  F --> H[GeneralizedSignupFlow]
  G --> I[SignupForm]
  J[PortfolioPage] --> K[BookingCalendar]
  J --> L[AvailabilityManager]
  J --> M[BookingManager]
  K --> N[api/bookings]
  L --> N
  M --> N
```

## 4. Key Features

### Functionality Overview
- Photographer discovery and search
- Comprehensive onboarding flow for photographers
- Interactive booking calendar
- Availability management for photographers
- Booking request management
- Portfolio creation and management

### Implementation Highlights
- **Landing Page**: Features an animated interface with photographer discovery and search functionality
- **Onboarding Flow**: Multi-step process for photographer registration and profile creation
- **Portfolio Management**: Complete suite of tools for photographers to manage their presence
- **Booking System**: Interactive calendar for scheduling and managing bookings

### Feature Architecture
The application's feature architecture demonstrates a modular approach:

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
  [*] --> LandingPage
  LandingPage --> Search: User searches
  LandingPage --> PhotographerProfile: User clicks photographer
  PhotographerProfile --> BookingCalendar: User books
  BookingCalendar --> Confirmation: Booking confirmed
  PhotographerProfile --> Onboarding: Photographer edits
  Onboarding --> PortfolioCreation: Profile created
  PortfolioCreation --> PortfolioPage: Portfolio live
  PortfolioPage --> AvailabilityManager: Manage availability
  PortfolioPage --> BookingManager: Manage bookings
  Confirmation --> [*]
  PortfolioPage --> [*]
```
